news.title: Godrej Capital to offer flexi-repayments, longer tenor loans against property for SMEs
news.para: ​The non-bank financier, which is among the youngest of the lending companies having entered in late 2020, will let borrowers from the Small and Medium Enterprises (SME) segment 'design' their own earnest monthly installments, as per an official statement.

news.title: Don't harass citizens with 'pending' issues of sale deed: Gujarat revenue department
news.para: In the latest notification dated June 28, the superintendent of stamps, Jenu Devan, has instructed its officers to stop registering any sale deed if the supporting documents are found to be incomplete.

news.title: Over 500 illegal constructions demolished in three months: Bihar minister
news.para: He said the bulldozer will continue to work against illegal setups in the state and asked the MLCs to lodge a complaint to the circle officer, if they know about any such encroachment on government land.

news.title: PNB Housing to seek shareholders' nod next month to raise Rs 12,000 crore in debt
news.para: The housing finance company promoted by the city-headquartered state-owned lender Punjab National Bank (PNB) is scheduled to convene its annual general meeting (AGM) next month on July 26.

news.title: UltraTech Cement paying for Russian coal in Chinese yuan
news.para: UltraTech is bringing in 157,000 tonnes of coal from Russian producer SUEK that loaded on the bulk carrier MV Mangas from the Russian Far East port of Vanino, the document showed.

news.title: Sebi bans Parsvnath Developers from securities market for six months
news.para: The company has been directed to pay the fine within 45 days, the Securities and Exchange Board of India (Sebi) said in an order.

news.title: UK house price growth slows slightly in June: Nationwide
news.para: House prices in June were 0.3% higher than in May, when they rose 0.9%. Compared with June 2021, prices were 10.7% higher, a slowdown from annual growth of 11.2% in May.

news.title: Varun Jaipuria of Varun Beverages buys farmhouse at Delhi's Westend Green for Rs 120 crore
news.para: Property experts said that more people are looking at farmhouses amid the restrictions due to Covid-19. After being stuck at home during the lockdowns, wealthy businessmen and executives are looking for large homes.

news.title: New Zealand central bank's chief economist warns housing no longer one-way bet
news.para: Conway said slower overall population growth and changes in taxation make it less attractive to invest in housing while policy designed to enable higher housing density are all altering the property market dynamics.

news.title: GST Council recommendations related to real estate and allied industries
news.para: GST exemption on renting of residential dwelling to business entities (registered persons) has been withdrawn. Sale of land after leveling, laying down of drainage lines etc. is sale of land and does not attract GST.

news.title: Despite reminders, no action on illegal buildings in Ludhiana
news.para: ​The chief vigilance officer has also sought report from the building branch and entire responsibility has been fixed on one of the building inspectors of the said zone.

news.title: Transition period ends amid upkeep worries in Gurugram colonies
news.para: The 15-day transition period during which the developers of these colonies were to assist the civic body ends on the day, but MCG hasn’t deployed any staff to ensure smooth maintenance services, they said.

news.title: Coimbatore corporation ropes in assistant engineers to speed up building plan approvals
news.para: Since there is only an assistant town planning officer for each ward, according to an official source, the civic body has decided to strengthen the building approval process by deploying around 45 engineers at the ward level.

news.title: Nashik civic body brings 13,000 new properties under tax net
news.para: NMC officials said that inclusion of these properties under the tax net will help the civic body to get additional Rs 17 crore property tax every fiscal.

news.title: Not taken over, but Gurugram civic body set to roll out essential services for colony highrises
news.para: The civic body recently took over Sushant Lok-2 and 3, Malibu Towne, Vipul World, Rosewood City, Uppal Southend, Ardee City, Greenwood City and Mayfield Garden.
